ContainedObjects.Description:
Fate tokens have light and darks sides. When a character has more "light side" fate, then the player is Lightbound. More dark side means Darkbound. Equal fate means Unbound. No fate means Fateless (Unbound to me as well)

LB = Lightbound effect (white sun icon)
DB = Darkbound effect (black sun icon)
UB = Unbound effect or Fateless effect

0.title: TTS Tips
0.body:
Tips for playing TALISMAN on TTS

- Use your Character Sheet to keep your things in order.
- Lock your Character Card on your Character Sheet
- Lock the board pieces if using expansions
- Right Click on Figures to tint them to your respective colour
- You can use tinted counters (Components - Tools) for counting Strength Craft and Life "cones", but personally I recommend using the cones themselves
- Maybe you know this but you can shuffle the contents of the bag themselves by shuffling the bag (For selecting random characters from the bag)
- Keep Spell cards face-down. Peek (hover cursor and alt-shift) it if necessary
- To "change alignment", change the state of the alignment card with 1, 2, and 3
